Long7 writes me that Kernahan (a famous critic), to whom he showed Despair,8 wrote him: "Reviewers who like it will hail it as genius.... Those who don't like [it] will say that it is extremely unpleasant....It is meant, I assume, to be the work of a criminal maniac, and as such is very admirably done" etc.9 Silly but flattering on the whole. Be